# Loading Consistency

## Rule

**Use the unified border-circle loading components from `@/components/ui/page-loading` for all loading states.** Same style as patient My Appointments — applied everywhere.

## Components

| Component | Use case | Placement |
|-----------|----------|-----------|
| `FullPageLoading` | Route transitions (`loading.tsx`), Suspense fallbacks | Full screen, centered |
| `SectionLoading` | Data fetch within a page (card, section, main content) | Centered in section, with optional label |
| `LoadingSpinner` | Buttons, inline (size: `sm` \| `md` \| `lg`) | Inline with content |
| `PageLoadingSkeleton` | List/card pages (search, clinics, pharmacies, labs) | Full page layout |

## Placement

- **Full-page**: Centered vertically and horizontally, `min-h-screen`
- **Section**: Centered in container, `min-h-[200px]` or `min-h-[280px]` for dashboard pages
- **Inline/buttons**: Next to button text, use `className="me-2"` for RTL-safe spacing

## Implementation

- **Route `loading.tsx`**: `export default function Loading() { return <FullPageLoading /> }`
- **List pages** (search, clinics, labs, pharmacies, nurses): Use `PageLoadingSkeleton`
- **Detail pages** (doctors/[id], clinics/[id], etc.): Use `SectionLoading` with `label` and `minHeight`
- **Inline/buttons**: Use `LoadingSpinner` with `size="sm"` for icons, `size="md"` for section headers

## Do Not

- Use raw `Loader2` with `animate-spin` — use `LoadingSpinner` instead
- Use plain text "Loading..." without a spinner
- Return `null` from `loading.tsx` — use `FullPageLoading`
- Mix different spinner styles — all use the border-circle (border-b-2)
